				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Do bards get pets?<a name="36819"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 27 04 4:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Cinda's is a &quot;faction song,&quot; and NOT used for Crowd Control (CC).  It has several uses.  Let's say, you need a certain level of faction to do a turn-in for a quest.  (Your faction shows when you &quot;con&quot; or right-click a mob.  The color is it's level relative to you, and the &quot;Scowls at you, ready to attack&quot; or &quot;regards you Amiably&quot; etc. is your faction.)  Generally, the faction song will raise you from one faction level to the next higher.  (Not always the case.  There are specific numbers involved, maybe someone will post them?)  NOTHING will make a KOS (kill on sight--&quot;Scowls at you, ready to attack&quot<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />mob like you.  BUT, if the merchants in a city won't trade with you, or something like that, sometimes singing faction song on them will convince them, hehe.
<br />

<br />
The Mez songs have level caps on them, or maximum levels for the mobs you can mez.  You generally get upgrades to them by the time you start getting mobs you can't mez.  Although, there are some gaps which makes things kind of a pain.  At lvl 59, for example, I often encountered mobs when grouped that I could not mez, because they were higher than lvl 57, the cap for the song I was using.  
<br />

<br />
lvl 15, Kelin's Lucid Lullabye, String, mobs up to level 30
<br />
lvl 28 Chrisson's Pixie Strike, Wind, up to lvl 45
<br />
lvl 40 Sionache's Dream, Wind, up to lvl 53
<br />
lvl 53 Song of Twilight, Wind, up to lvl 55
<br />
(Suck-a$ Gap here)
<br />
lvl 58 Dreams of Ayone, Wind, up to lvl 57
<br />
(Gap)
<br />
lvl 60 Ancient: (meaning very rare) Lullabye of Shadow, Singing, up to lvl 59
<br />
(Gap)
<br />
lvl 62 Dreams of Thule, Wind, up to lvl 62
<br />
(Gap)
<br />
lvl 64 Dreams of Terris, Wind, up to lvl 65
<br />
lvl 65 Lullabye of Morrel, Singing, up to lvl 68
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, the gaps make you less useful to groups, if you are hunting mobs you can't mez.  In such cases, a higher level Bard is needed, or an Enchanter.
<br />

<br />
Another useful tool we have is Lull.  Your lvl 8 song, Kelin's Ligubrious Lament can be used to &quot;single pull&quot; mobs, i.e. make sure they come at you one at a time.  Read the guide <a href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Guide.aspx?id=8&amp;ForumID=132">Anatomy of a Train:  a Newbie Guide to Aggro and Pulling</a> for more details about lulling and pulling.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Scherzo Glissando <BR>
Maestro, Molto Espressivo</span></td>
