				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Do bards get pets?<a name="38289"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 5 04 10:31 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Practice some charming amd mezzing on stuff that's green or light blue to you. When I was lvl 27 and got my first charm, my wind instruments were so bad that I couldn't even get the song off half the time without missing a note, my brass was so bad that i couldn't even USE the fear song until 3 or 4 lvls later. I wasn't asking questions to other bards, I wasn't practicing my instruments, I just figured the skills would stay ahead of the curve and by the time I hit 32 or so, my skills were total poop. Do yourself and your group a favor, and practice instrument skills overnight in PoK or somewhere else that's safe. You have to practice your weapon skills too but don't worry about that as much, you must must must keep those instruments maxed out!!! Practice and screw around in areas where you won't die, then try it on some real mobs, then go screw around in areas where you CAN die. Dying is healthy in EQ, it usually means you learned something, and if you didn't, it usually means you should have. 
<br />
</span></td>
